    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Pipe webhook payloads with Google Drive and log the results\n\n**Pattern:** Webhook Pipeline · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nPipe webhook payloads with Google Drive and log the results. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual triggers is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Keep Valid Jobs → Route by Work Type → Process 'standard' → Google Sheets → Merge Routed Work → Cap Batch Volume → Sort Jobs Newest First → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to webhook pipeline without manual effort\n- Anyone automating triggers in productivity\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "72a589da-9842-d2d0-b9d4-af30c2945a14",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -290
      ],
      "id": "e0d7cb0f-e3cd-e143-ec46-863f2bf5ca49",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -290
      ],
      "id": "f77e86e0-befa-b2fc-4420-53ebd84546d6",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your triggers process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
